    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen opened in neovim, named subroutine signature args highlight as possible errors. I took a quick look at the regex for perlSubPrototypeError in /usr/share/nvim/runtime/syntax/perl.vim and couldn't work out exactly what needs changing. For now, I have just commented out this line in my install as a quick fix:\r\n\r\n`\" hi def link perlSubPrototypeError   Error`\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nSample Perl. Open in Neovim to see what I mean - $arg is marked as an error.\r\n\r\n`#!/usr/bin/perl\r\nuse v5.36;\r\n\r\nsub whatever($arg) {\r\n    ...\r\n}`\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nNot highlight the $arg as an error\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.7.2 2.1.0-beta3\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNo - vim has correct highlighting\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nKubuntu\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nKonsole\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\napt, I think",
